# CafeCanvas — Cursor Project Rules
# Multi-Tenant SaaS Restaurant Operating System
# Stack: Next.js 16 · Supabase · Tailwind CSS 4 · TypeScript (strict)

## PROJECT IDENTITY

CafeCanvas is a multi-tenant SaaS restaurant OS for the Indian market.
- Super Admin creates tenant (restaurant) accounts
- Tenants get: admin dashboard, menu management, billing, analytics
- Customers see: public digital storefront at [slug].cafecanvas.bar
- Staff use: POS + Kitchen Display System (KDS)

## CANONICAL TECH STACK (DO NOT DEVIATE)

| Layer | Technology |
|-------|-----------|
| Frontend | Next.js 16 (App Router), React 19, TypeScript strict |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS 4 with CSS variables (NO inline styles) |
| Auth | Supabase Auth with JWT tenant claims hook |
| Database | Supabase PostgreSQL (22 tables, RLS enforced) |
| Edge Functions | Supabase Deno functions |
| State | Zustand (cart, order, theme, table stores) |
| Icons | Lucide React only |
| Charts | Recharts |
| Toast | Sonner |
| Animation | Framer Motion (respect prefers-reduced-motion) |
| Fonts | Google Fonts (Inter, Outfit) |
| Hosting | Vercel (Mumbai bom1 region) |

## GLOBAL RULES (NON-NEGOTIABLE)

1. **TypeScript strict** — NO `any` types, ever
2. **Supabase only** — NO direct Postgres connections in app code
3. **Tailwind CSS 4** — NO inline styles. Use CSS variables
4. **`@/` imports** — NO relative `../../` imports
5. **Server Components default** — Client components marked `"use client"`
6. **RLS is security** — Every table has RLS. Tenant scoping via JWT claims
7. **i18n** — All user-facing strings support en + hi (Hindi)
8. **INR currency** — GST in paise (integer). CGST + SGST split required
9. **Mobile-first** — All UI works at 375px minimum
10. **Tests** — Write tests in `/tests/` for every new file
11. **Storefront Deployment Rule** — Storefronts are resolved dynamically via middleware routing. Store Admins execute a one-time deploy verification step, but the storefront is live and working at all times through real-time database synchronization.

